description:
One of the greatest artists ever, Johannes Vermeer painted only 34 known works. One of them is at the MIA, for a limited time. See it before it leaves on May 3, 2015. And, yes, it’s free.

Johannes Vermeer, Woman Reading a Letter, c. 1663, Oil on canvas, 46.5 cm × 39 cm, Rijksmuseum, Amsterdam, on loan from the City of Amsterdam van der Hoop Bequest
title: Vermeer Masterpiece in Focus, Of Us and Art: The 100 Videos Project, Episode 11
